00:34:22,660 --> 00:34:24,200
Okay sure.

553
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:27,110
No need to mention panties or car sex.

554
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:29,850
We don't need to stoop to that level, do we?

555
00:34:29,850 --> 00:34:31,070
Surely not!

556
00:34:32,020 --> 00:34:34,290
But what if he goes online and accuses us...

557
00:34:34,290 --> 00:34:37,000
Just give him a good severance.

558
00:34:38,350 --> 00:34:40,520
How was Da-song today?

559
00:34:41,150 --> 00:34:42,520
He was fine.

560
00:34:43,570 --> 00:34:45,280
-So class is finished?    -Yes.

561
00:34:45,990 --> 00:34:48,760
Jessica, the last time you came,

562
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:51,230
our driver gave you a ride, right?

563
00:34:51,230 --> 00:34:52,240
That's right.

564
00:34:52,240 --> 00:34:54,040
This may be an odd question,

565
00:34:54,670 --> 00:34:56,640
but nothing happened then?

566
00:34:56,640 --> 00:34:58,090
No, he was very nice.

567
00:34:58,090 --> 00:34:59,960
I told him to go to Hyehwa Station,

568
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:03,470
but he insisted on driving me home.

569
00:35:03,470 --> 00:35:06,610
That jerk! He took you home late at night?

570
00:35:06,610 --> 00:35:07,960
Revealing where you live?

571
00:35:09,130 --> 00:35:10,960
No, I got off at Hyehwa.

572
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:13,720
Oh, good girl. Very good.

573
00:35:13,720 --> 00:35:15,250
Jessica nice...

574
00:35:15,830 --> 00:35:17,730
Did something happen with him?

575
00:35:18,430 --> 00:35:23,210
He won't be working for us any more. A slightly shameful incident.

576
00:35:23,990 --> 00:35:25,700
What incident?

577
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:28,270
Oh, you don't need to know.

578
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:33,940
But I'm surprised. He was so gentlemanly and cool.

579
00:35:33,940 --> 00:35:37,380
Jessica, you're too young and innocent!

580
00:35:37,380 --> 00:35:38,880
You have a lot to learn about people.

581
00:35:40,170 --> 00:35:45,050
But we were excited to have such a young, hip driver, too.

582
00:35:45,050 --> 00:35:48,420
But isn't an older driver better?

583
00:35:48,420 --> 00:35:51,750
That's true. They drive better, have better manners.

584
00:35:52,610 --> 00:35:55,320
My father's brother had a driver just like that.

585
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:59,900
Mr. Kim. He was so congenial and nice,

586
00:35:59,900 --> 00:36:03,060
I used to call him Uncle when I was young.

587
00:36:03,060 --> 00:36:04,510
You know a man like that?

588
00:36:04,510 --> 00:36:07,030
Yes, he was so mild-mannered.

589
00:36:09,160 --> 00:36:12,490
Oh, but my relatives relocated to Chicago.

590
00:36:14,030 --> 00:36:15,740
I wonder if Mr. Kim's free now?

591
00:36:16,740 --> 00:36:19,590
I'm really interested! Could I meet him?

592
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:21,900
Really?

593
00:36:21,900 --> 00:36:23,680
I don't trust anyone now.

594
00:36:24,340 --> 00:36:26,860
I only trust someone recommended by a person I know well.

595
00:36:27,470 --> 00:36:30,370
But if you've known him so long,

596
00:36:30,370 --> 00:36:32,050
I'd feel much more at ease.

597
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:36,200
Do you really want to meet him?

598
00:36:37,250 --> 00:36:38,390
I'm deadly serious.

599
00:36:39,170 --> 00:36:42,380
This chain of recommendations is best.

600
00:36:43,150 --> 00:36:44,150
How should I describe it?

601
00:36:44,810 --> 00:36:45,990
A belt of trust?

602
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:47,830
-This one's different.    -Here.

603
00:36:47,830 --> 00:36:48,490
Oh, right.

604
00:36:48,490 --> 00:36:49,550
And this one.

605
00:36:50,310 --> 00:36:51,850
Looks like a touch screen now.

606
00:36:51,850 --> 00:36:54,890
It's not touch, it says you have to turn it.

607
00:36:54,890 --> 00:36:56,470
Wow, this thing?

608
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:58,160
Sir?

609
00:36:58,540 --> 00:37:00,160
Taking our time, are we?

610
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:04,780
This is a nice car.

611
00:37:07,170 --> 00:37:09,260
This is en it! Come over here.

612
00:37:12,550 --> 00:37:14,200
He's in a meeting now.

613
00:37:19,570 --> 00:37:21,520
Have a seat and wait here.

614
00:37:30,340 --> 00:37:31,420
Hello, nice to meet...

615
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:38,490
But is it compatible with a phone?

616
00:37:38,490 --> 00:37:44,590
Oh, not with a phone. You need more computing power.

617
00:37:46,260 --> 00:37:50,050
This isn't any sort of test, so don't be nervous.

618
00:37:51,500 --> 00:37:54,470
I was worn out at the office, so I came out for a bit.

619
00:37:54,470 --> 00:37:55,990
I understand.

620
00:37:56,570 --> 00:37:59,440
Constant chatter, all that bother.

621
00:37:59,440 --> 00:38:00,950
At least the car is peaceful.

622
00:38:03,560 --> 00:38:04,320
Thank you.

623
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:07,150
You seem to know the road well?

624
00:38:07,150 --> 00:38:09,880
Anything below the 38th parallel.

625
00:38:10,610 --> 00:38:13,800
After 30 years behind the wheel, the car almost drives itself.

626
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:16,250
I respect those who work in one field for a long time.

627
00:38:17,310 --> 00:38:20,070
Well, to be honest this is a simple vocation.

628
00:38:20,070 --> 00:38:22,860
But... the head of a household,

629
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:24,870
the leader of a company?

630
00:38:25,630 --> 00:38:28,340
Or else just a lonely man

631
00:38:28,340 --> 00:38:30,140
setting off on the road each morning...

632
00:38:31,100 --> 00:38:32,870
It's companionship of a sort,

633
00:38:33,540 --> 00:38:36,380
so that's how I've approached each day.

634
00:38:36,380 --> 00:38:38,140
The years sure pass quickly.

635
00:38:42,150 --> 00:38:43,890
Sure enough, your cornering is excellent.

636
00:38:46,580 --> 00:38:51,020
Well, it may look simple, but it's one of the fundamentals.

637
00:38:51,830 --> 00:38:56,050
She may look like a sheep, but inside, she's a fox.

638
00:38:56,860 --> 00:38:59,440
Sometimes she acts like she owns the house.

639
00:39:00,280 --> 00:39:01,440
Right.

640
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:05,360
Of all the people in that house, she's lived there the longest.

641
00:39:06,020 --> 00:39:09,720
She was housekeeper to the architect Namgoong,

642
00:39:09,720 --> 00:39:13,580
but then she went on to work for this family.

643
00:39:14,580 --> 00:39:16,380
When the architect moved out,

644
00:39:16,380 --> 00:39:18,840
he introduced this woman to Park's family,

645
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:22,640
telling them, "This is a great housekeeper, you should hire her."

646
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:26,170
So she survived a change of ownership.

647
00:39:26,170 --> 00:39:28,730
She won't give up good job easily.

648
00:39:29,480 --> 00:39:32,600
To extract a woman like that, we need to prepare well.

649
00:39:34,370 --> 00:39:36,350
Right, we need a plan.

650
00:39:38,130 --> 00:39:41,030
I want to eat peaches. I like peaches best.

651
00:39:41,950 --> 00:39:43,460
Why not ask for some?

652
00:39:43,460 --> 00:39:46,720
No peaches at our house. It's a forbidden fruit.

653
00:39:54,770 --> 00:39:57,850
So according to what Da-hye told me,

654
00:39:57,850 --> 00:40:00,490
she's got a massively serious allergy to peaches.

655
00:40:00,490 --> 00:40:01,930
You know that fuzz on a peach's skin?

656
00:40:02,490 --> 00:40:05,470
If she's anywhere near it, she gets a full body rash,

657
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:12,920
has trouble breathing, asthma, a total meltdown!

658
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:21,940
No no, there weren't any peaches anywhere.

659
00:40:23,860 --> 00:40:25,830
That's what I'm saying!

660
00:40:26,510 --> 00:40:29,260
Usually when I get symptoms like this,

661
00:40:29,260 --> 00:40:32,100
I run to my room and take my medicine,

662
00:40:33,220 --> 00:40:35,750
but it was so sudden,

663
00:40:35,750 --> 00:40:37,950
I wasn't sure where I left it.

664
00:40:37,950 --> 00:40:42,680
Madame, this woman behind me, is that?

665
00:40:43,300 --> 00:40:45,240
Oh, it's our housekeeper!

666
00:40:45,240 --> 00:40:47,240
So it's true. Oh, how sad.

667
00:40:48,010 --> 00:40:50,270
I wasn't sure if that was really her.

668
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:54,350
I've only seen her a couple times in the living room.

669
00:40:55,830 --> 00:40:57,420
This was in the hospital?

670
00:40:57,420 --> 00:41:01,200
A few days ago I went for my annual medical exam.

671
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:04,120
I took a selfie for my wife,

672
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:05,670
and there she was behind me.

673
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:08,660
Is she talking on the phone there?

674
00:41:10,430 --> 00:41:11,880
Anyway. I wasn't trying to eavesdrop...

675
00:41:11,880 --> 00:41:13,880
I wasn't trying to eavesdrop...

676
00:41:13,880 --> 00:41:15,800
but her words came through clearly!

677
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:17,630
-So I couldn't help but..    -Cut, cut!

678
00:41:17,630 --> 00:41:20,640
Dad, your emotions are up to here.

679
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:22,640
Bring them down to about there.

680
00:41:23,240 --> 00:41:26,000
...so I couldn't help but overhear.

681
00:41:26,000 --> 00:41:28,560
Keep it focused!

682
00:41:30,170 --> 00:41:33,450
What I'm trying to say is, it's just that,

683
00:41:34,020 --> 00:41:36,350
your housekeeper's voice is quite loud, you know?

684
00:41:37,150 --> 00:41:40,060
I understand, it's all right. Just tell me, okay?

685
00:41:40,690 --> 00:41:43,630
She said she got diagnosed with active TB,

686
00:41:43,630 --> 00:41:46,220
and she was shouting on the phone,

687
00:41:46,220 --> 00:41:48,870
so upset she could barely control herself!

688
00:41:48,870 --> 00:41:51,340
Tuberculosis? Come on...

689
00:41:51,340 --> 00:41:56,340
It's true, she phoned someone saying she had active TB.

690
00:41:57,060 --> 00:42:01,690
Do people still get TB?

691
00:42:02,110 --> 00:42:02,740
Dad...

692
00:42:03,230 --> 00:42:07,490
Back in the day, people used to buy Christmas Seals, right?

693
00:42:08,470 --> 00:42:09,900
Feels like a bygone era.

694
00:42:09,900 --> 00:42:11,560
But I saw it on the internet.

695
00:42:11,560 --> 00:42:15,520
Korea has the #1 rate of TB of all the OECD countries.

696
00:42:15,520 --> 00:42:19,140
But she's still working, as if nothing's wrong.

697
00:42:19,140 --> 00:42:21,190
With a kid like Da-song in the house.

698
00:42:21,190 --> 00:42:23,980
So you've got a young kid like Da-song in the house,

699
00:42:24,590 --> 00:42:26,560
and a TB patient is doing dishes,

700
00:42:26,560 --> 00:42:27,860
cooking, spraying spittle...

701
00:42:27,860 --> 00:42:29,040
Stop it, please!

702
00:42:33,900 --> 00:42:35,280
Dad: arriving in 3 mins.

703
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:25,730
If you get the chance, this'll be icing on the cake.

704
00:43:56,900 --> 00:43:58,260
Madame

705
00:43:58,260 --> 00:44:00,200
2nd floor sauna room.

706
00:44:00,200 --> 00:44:01,200
Don't let anyone know

707
00:44:11,810 --> 00:44:12,980
-Have a seat.    -Yes.

708
00:44:15,560 --> 00:44:16,230
Mr. Kim.

709
00:44:16,660 --> 00:44:20,080
Please don't tell any of this to my husband, okay?

710
00:44:20,850 --> 00:44:21,930
Understood.

711
00:44:21,930 --> 00:44:25,880
If he hears I brought a TB patient to our home,

712
00:44:26,820 --> 00:44:29,580
I'll be hanged and quartered!

713
00:44:29,580 --> 00:44:31,110
Don't worry, Madame.

714
00:44:31,870 --> 00:44:34,640
And if I may presume to say one thing.

715
00:44:35,330 --> 00:44:38,120
I have no feelings against that woman.

716
00:44:39,020 --> 00:44:44,370
I felt I had to speak up for the sake of

717
00:44:44,370 --> 00:44:46,080
public health and hygiene.

718
00:44:46,660 --> 00:44:50,240
But this could be seen as snitching or...

719
00:44:50,240 --> 00:44:51,720
Don't you worry.

720
00:44:51,720 --> 00:44:54,430
I won't mention the TB.

721
00:44:54,430 --> 00:44:56,110
I'll just make up some excuse to dismiss her.

722
00:44:56,950 --> 00:44:57,890
Simply and quietly.

723
00:45:00,090 --> 00:45:02,100
It's a proven method. That's the best.

724
00:45:02,930 --> 00:45:04,230
Okay, then.

725
00:45:15,730 --> 00:45:18,230
Have you... washed your hands?

726
00:46:04,380 --> 00:46:05,240
Mr. Kim,

727
00:46:06,140 --> 00:46:08,660
do you know a good braised ribs place?

728
00:46:08,660 --> 00:46:10,430
Somewhere close by.

729
00:46:10,430 --> 00:46:11,330
Sure.

730
00:46:11,890 --> 00:46:15,190
-Then you'll be eating out?    -That's right.

731
00:46:16,230 --> 00:46:19,480
Why such a craving for braised ribs today?

732
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:22,400
Our old housekeeper made delicious ribs.

733
00:46:22,400 --> 00:46:26,190
The one who quit this week?

734
00:46:27,100 --> 00:46:30,610
My wife wouldn't even tell me why she quit.

735
00:46:33,460 --> 00:46:38,160
Sure, it's easy enough to hire a new one.

736
00:46:39,670 --> 00:46:44,540
Still, it's a shame. She was a great housekeeper

737
00:46:44,540 --> 00:46:45,510
I see.

738
00:46:45,510 --> 00:46:48,110
She kept the house in great shape,

739
00:46:48,110 --> 00:46:50,370
and she knew never to cross the line.

740
00:46:51,410 --> 00:46:53,610
I can't stand people who cross the line.

741
00:46:54,680 --> 00:46:56,990
Perhaps just one weak point?

742
00:46:58,170 --> 00:46:59,800
Eating too much.

743
00:46:59,800 --> 00:47:01,920
She always ate enough for two.

744
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:07,020
But considering all the work she did...

745
00:47:07,640 --> 00:47:11,980
Then you better find someone new. A new housekeeper.

746
00:47:12,750 --> 00:47:14,360
We're in trouble now.

747
00:47:14,840 --> 00:47:18,830
In a week, our house will be a trash can.

748
00:47:20,130 --> 00:47:22,370
My clothes will start to smell.

749
00:47:24,300 --> 00:47:26,940
My wife has no talent for housework.

750
00:47:27,400 --> 00:47:30,010
She's bad at cleaning, and her cooking's awful.

751
00:47:31,540 --> 00:47:33,070
Still, you love her, right?

752
00:47:41,350 --> 00:47:44,300
Of course. I love her.

753
00:47:45,450 --> 00:47:46,910
We'll call it love.

754
00:47:49,200 --> 00:47:50,710
Then would this help?

755
00:47:55,180 --> 00:47:57,680
The Care? What is this?

756
00:47:57,680 --> 00:48:00,040
I just recently found out about them.

757
00:48:00,040 --> 00:48:04,550
How to describe it? It's like a membership service.

758
00:48:05,550 --> 00:48:07,880
The company provides veteran-grade

759
00:48:07,980 --> 00:48:12,080
help to VIP customers such as you.

760
00:48:12,190 --> 00:48:18,090
For example maids, caregivers. or drivers like myself.

761
00:48:19,040 --> 00:48:21,080
You can tell from the card they're high-class.

762
00:48:21,900 --> 00:48:23,020
Cool design.

763
00:48:24,760 --> 00:48:26,810
Then how do you know about this company?

764
00:48:26,810 --> 00:48:30,750
They contacted me as a veteran-grade driver.

765
00:48:31,440 --> 00:48:33,170
You might say they scouted me?

766
00:48:34,970 --> 00:48:40,990
But when their call came I had already arranged to meet with you.

767
00:48:42,640 --> 00:48:44,000
I see...

768
00:48:45,150 --> 00:48:47,940
You turned down this famous company to work for me.

769
00:48:48,820 --> 00:48:50,220
I won't forget that.

770
00:48:51,720 --> 00:48:53,260
Son of a bitch!

771
00:48:55,980 --> 00:49:00,250
Anyway, I can give this card to my wife, right?

772
00:49:00,250 --> 00:49:02,090
Yes, that's why I brought it up.

773
00:49:02,090 --> 00:49:03,990
No need to mention me.

774
00:49:04,680 --> 00:49:08,690
You can tell her you found the company yourself.

775
00:49:09,390 --> 00:49:10,510
Sure.

776
00:49:10,980 --> 00:49:13,410
Thanks to you I can play the good husband.

777
00:49:13,410 --> 00:49:17,490
On the back, there's a number for consultations.

778
00:49:18,230 --> 00:49:19,470
Tell her to call there...

779
00:49:19,470 --> 00:49:20,660
Eyes on the road!

780
00:49:25,980 --> 00:49:28,840
Hello, this is Senior Advisor Yeo of The Care.

781
00:49:29,490 --> 00:49:32,720
Yes, this is The Care's main office?

782
00:49:32,730 --> 00:49:33,730
Yes.

783
00:49:33,740 --> 00:49:37,270
If she wanted, she'd be a fucking great con artist.

784
00:49:37,270 --> 00:49:39,220
Isn't her voice tone great? Takes after me.

785
00:49:41,220 --> 00:49:44,030
From what I've heard, it's a full membership service?

786
00:49:44,030 --> 00:49:48,010
So you're not currently a member, I assume?

787
00:49:48,010 --> 00:49:50,590
That's right, What steps do I need to take?

788
00:49:50,590 --> 00:49:54,820
We'll just need to receive a few documents from you.

789
00:49:54,820 --> 00:49:57,430
Are you ready to write this down?

790
00:49:57,960 --> 00:50:02,310
Your family register, citizenship ID cards...

791
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:06,040
documents to prove your income level,

792
00:50:06,700 --> 00:50:09,010
i.e the title to your property, etc.

793
00:50:09,010 --> 00:50:10,980
-Our property title?    -Yes.

794
00:50:19,830 --> 00:50:21,480
Wow, peaches!

795
00:50:21,480 --> 00:50:22,960
You have some too, Mr. Kevin.

796
00:50:23,820 --> 00:50:24,790
Thank you.

797
00:50:33,600 --> 00:50:36,510
Leave it outside the door next time.

798
00:50:36,510 --> 00:50:38,320
-And knock!    -Yes.

799
00:50:41,390 --> 00:50:43,090
No entering during my lesson!

800
00:50:43,090 --> 00:50:44,030
Yes, miss!

801
00:50:46,570 --> 00:50:48,140
Park Da-song!

802
00:50:48,140 --> 00:50:49,400
Daddy!

803
00:50:49,400 --> 00:50:50,610
Where are you?

804
00:50:55,360 --> 00:50:56,600
Daddy!

805
00:50:56,600 --> 00:50:57,690
Son!

806
00:50:57,690 --> 00:50:58,810
Walkie talkies!

807
00:50:59,330 --> 00:51:01,460
Walkie talkies!

808
00:51:01,460 --> 00:51:03,680
Who do you like better, your dad or the walkie talkie?

809
00:51:05,380 --> 00:51:07,850
Da-song, how could you run out from your lesson?

810
00:51:08,540 --> 00:51:11,830
When did you buy all this?

811
00:51:11,830 --> 00:51:13,170
It's no big deal.

812
00:51:13,170 --> 00:51:13,910
Huh?

813
00:51:17,320 --> 00:51:17,840
Huh?

814
00:51:18,970 --> 00:51:20,000
What is it?

815
00:51:23,110 --> 00:51:24,340
What's he doing now?

816
00:51:25,730 --> 00:51:26,830
Da-song, don't do that!

817
00:51:27,880 --> 00:51:30,110
It's the same! They smell the same!

818
00:51:30,730 --> 00:51:33,620
What are you talking about? Go up to Jessica.

819
00:51:34,480 --> 00:51:37,840
Jessica smells like that, too.

820
00:51:39,300 --> 00:51:42,930
So do we all need to use different soap, now?

821
00:51:42,930 --> 00:51:46,870
Dad, we'll need to use different laundry soap, too.

822
00:51:46,870 --> 00:51:47,730
And fabric softener.

823
00:51:47,730 --> 00:51:51,140
You mean doing four separate loads of laundry each time?

824
00:51:52,490 --> 00:51:53,970
That's not it.

825
00:51:55,240 --> 00:51:56,970
It's the semi-basement smell.

826
00:51:58,230 --> 00:52:00,220
We need to leave this home to lose the smell.

827
00:52:04,510 --> 00:52:08,830
Anyway, aren't we fortunate to be worrying about things like this?

828
00:52:08,830 --> 00:52:09,940
Sure.

829
00:52:09,940 --> 00:52:12,440
In an age like ours,

830
00:52:13,310 --> 00:52:17,410
when an opening for a security
guard attracts 500 university graduates.

831
00:52:17,980 --> 00:52:21,010
Our entire family got hired!

832
00:52:21,010 --> 00:52:22,940
That's right, Dad!

833
00:52:23,890 --> 00:52:26,540
If we put our 4 salaries together?

834
00:52:26,540 --> 00:52:30,380
The amount of cash coming from that house into ours is immense!

835
00:52:31,570 --> 00:52:34,900
Let's offer a prayer of gratitude to the great Mr. Park.

836
00:52:34,900 --> 00:52:36,800
And to Min!

837
00:52:37,270 --> 00:52:39,430
Ki-woo, that friend of yours turned into such a fine guy,

838
00:52:39,430 --> 00:52:41,640
and thanks to him we're all...

839
00:52:41,640 --> 00:52:42,870
Fuck, not again!

840
00:52:42,870 --> 00:52:44,280
That asshole's dead.

841
00:52:50,040 --> 00:52:52,700
Ki-woo's on the rampage!

842
00:52:52,700 --> 00:52:53,990
Don't overdo it!

843
00:52:57,180 --> 00:52:58,910
Use this instead.

844
00:52:59,780 --> 00:53:00,930
Damn you!

845
00:53:06,570 --> 00:53:07,880
Get a fucking grip!

846
00:53:07,880 --> 00:53:09,080
Get a grip!

847
00:53:12,030 --> 00:53:12,980
Wow!

848
00:53:17,570 --> 00:53:19,360
It's a deluge!

849
00:53:36,070 --> 00:53:40,540
Current weather is clear, over. The clouds are moving.

850
00:53:40,540 --> 00:53:42,980
But they're not rain clouds, over.

851
00:53:42,980 --> 00:53:44,490
I hear you, over.

852
00:53:44,490 --> 00:53:48,370
Currently your sister's lip is pouting

853
00:53:48,370 --> 00:53:50,300
like a duck's bill.

854
00:53:50,950 --> 00:53:53,250
She's super annoyed, over.

855
00:53:53,990 --> 00:53:56,690
Can't I stay home and study English?

856
00:53:57,250 --> 00:53:58,430
And call Kevin?

857
00:53:59,990 --> 00:54:02,260
Hey! Don't make a scene just as we're leaving.

858
00:54:02,260 --> 00:54:04,710
If we have to go, let's have fun.

859
00:54:04,710 --> 00:54:07,560
Da-hye, this is no ordinary camping trip.

860
00:54:07,560 --> 00:54:08,280
That's right!

861
00:54:08,280 --> 00:54:10,480
How could you miss your brother's birthday?

862
00:54:10,480 --> 00:54:11,220
No way!

863
00:54:11,220 --> 00:54:13,070
Even your busy father is taking time off to go.

864
00:54:13,070 --> 00:54:16,120
Right! If you don't go, you'll regret it!

865
00:54:18,870 --> 00:54:21,040
Oh, right. You know the beam projector?

866
00:54:21,040 --> 00:54:22,350
The outdoor theater?

867
00:54:22,350 --> 00:54:24,060
Right, bring the outdoor beam projector.

868
00:54:24,060 --> 00:54:24,850
Yes.

869
00:54:24,850 --> 00:54:28,590
And look for Da-song's camping raincoat.

870
00:54:29,190 --> 00:54:30,910
He loves it when it rains.

871
00:54:31,580 --> 00:54:35,500
You remember now? Zoonie, Berry, and Fofoo.

872
00:54:35,500 --> 00:54:36,800
Zoome and Berry get this.

873
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:39,740
Yes, Natural Balance Original Ultra.

874
00:54:39,740 --> 00:54:41,760
Right, and for Foofoo...

875
00:54:42,370 --> 00:54:44,510
Kam-kamaboko. Japanese crab sticks.

876
00:54:44,510 --> 00:54:45,160
Yes.

877
00:54:45,160 --> 00:54:48,060
When you walk Zoonie, give him a long leash.

878
00:54:48,060 --> 00:54:51,180
He needs to run around to feel happy.

879
00:54:51,180 --> 00:54:53,740
He's like the canine version of Da-song!

880
00:55:19,620 --> 00:55:21,010
Son!

881
00:55:21,590 --> 00:55:24,160
Why are you lying down outside?

882
00:55:24,560 --> 00:55:26,930
Isn't he hot out there?

883
00:55:29,990 --> 00:55:32,220
I'm gazing at the sky from home.

884
00:55:34,390 --> 00:55:35,380
It's so great.

885
00:55:39,260 --> 00:55:41,630
Mom, want some water?

886
00:55:41,630 --> 00:55:42,950
There's sparkling, right?

887
00:55:42,950 --> 00:55:45,610
Ki-jung, some water?

888
00:55:45,610 --> 00:55:47,220
Telepathy... thank you.

889
00:56:09,790 --> 00:56:11,380
Whoa.

890
00:56:13,830 --> 00:56:16,300
Wow, all these varieties or alcohol.

891
00:56:17,580 --> 00:56:21,120
Dad! Let me add another to the mix!

892
00:56:23,710 --> 00:56:25,250
This is pretty classy.

893
00:56:26,320 --> 00:56:29,700
Rain falling on the lawn, as we sip our whiskey...

894
00:56:31,600 --> 00:56:35,860
Ki-woo, what's that yellow notebook you've been carrying?

895
00:56:37,020 --> 00:56:40,120
This? It's Da-hye's diary.

896
00:56:41,280 --> 00:56:42,120
Her diary?

897
00:56:42,780 --> 00:56:46,090
What a scumbag. How could you read her diary?

898
00:56:48,270 --> 00:56:52,300
Just so we can understand each other deeper.

899
00:56:52,300 --> 00:56:54,580
Fuck, are you two dating?

900
00:56:55,190 --> 00:56:59,190
I'm serious. She really likes me too.

901
00:57:01,340 --> 00:57:02,210
Awhile back...

902
00:57:03,750 --> 00:57:04,800
Never mind.

903
00:57:06,050 --> 00:57:08,540
When she enters university. I'll officially ask her out.

904
00:57:09,300 --> 00:57:10,210
Seriously.

905
00:57:15,270 --> 00:57:16,720
My son!

906
00:57:17,480 --> 00:57:21,480
Then this house will be your in-laws' house?

907
00:57:24,060 --> 00:57:25,490
That's right.

908
00:57:26,790 --> 00:57:29,490
Fuck, then I'm washing dishes at my daughter-in-law's?

909
00:57:29,490 --> 00:57:32,570
Sure, washing your daughter-in-law's socks!

910
00:57:44,760 --> 00:57:49,440
I like her. She's a good kid.

911
00:57:50,320 --> 00:57:54,160
She's pretty, but she's not wild.

912
00:57:56,520 --> 00:57:59,180
Well, now that we're daydreaming...

913
00:58:00,900 --> 00:58:02,730
If Da-hye and I marry,

914
00:58:03,640 --> 00:58:07,000
we can bring in actors to be my mom and dad.

915
00:58:08,240 --> 00:58:09,000
Look at her.

916
00:58:09,540 --> 00:58:12,710
She got so many jobs acting in weddings last year.

917
00:58:14,580 --> 00:58:17,250
even caught the bouquet from a bitch I've never met.

918
00:58:17,920 --> 00:58:20,960
If you get the bouquet, they pay an extra $10.

919
00:58:20,960 --> 00:58:23,120
That's how your acting got so good!

920
00:58:23,120 --> 00:58:26,310
Acting is one thing,

921
00:58:26,310 --> 00:58:28,770
but this family is so gullible, right?

922
00:58:28,770 --> 00:58:31,000
The madame especially.

923
00:58:31,000 --> 00:58:32,370
You said it.

924
00:58:34,520 --> 00:58:37,220
She's so naive, and nice.

925
00:58:38,170 --> 00:58:40,240
She's rich, but still nice.

926
00:58:40,240 --> 00:58:42,640
Not "rich, but still nice."

927
00:58:42,640 --> 00:58:45,970
"Nice because she's rich." You know?

928
00:58:49,790 --> 00:58:53,150
Hell, if I had all this money.

929
00:58:54,540 --> 00:58:58,130
I'd be nice too!

930
00:58:58,130 --> 00:58:59,380
Even nicer!

931
00:59:00,480 --> 00:59:02,400
That's true. Your mom's right.

932
00:59:02,830 --> 00:59:05,240
Rich people are naive. No resentments.

933
00:59:05,240 --> 00:59:07,700
No creases on them.

934
00:59:07,700 --> 00:59:10,460
It all gets ironed out. Money is an iron.

935
00:59:11,150 --> 00:59:13,690
Those creases all get smoothed out.

936
00:59:13,690 --> 00:59:14,740
Hey, Ki-woo.

937
00:59:15,850 --> 00:59:20,250
You know that driver, Yoon? Was it Yoon?

938
00:59:21,220 --> 00:59:23,790
The driver before me.

939
00:59:23,790 --> 00:59:25,050
Yeah, Yoon.

940
00:59:25,050 --> 00:59:29,690
He must be working somewhere else now, right?

941
00:59:29,690 --> 00:59:32,160
Sure, he must be.

942
00:59:32,160 --> 00:59:35,080
He's young, got a nice physique.

943
00:59:35,800 --> 00:59:38,930
He must've found a better job.

944
00:59:38,930 --> 00:59:40,930
Fucking hell!

945
00:59:42,140 --> 00:59:44,040
What's with her now?

946
00:59:44,700 --> 00:59:50,500
We're the ones who need help. Worry about us, okay?

947
00:59:51,230 --> 00:59:54,310
Dad! Come on, Dad!

948
00:59:54,730 --> 00:59:59,210
Just focus on us, okay? On us!

949
00:59:59,210 --> 01:00:03,640
Not Driver Yoon, but me, please.

950
01:00:03,640 --> 01:00:05,650
Awesome timing, huh?

951
01:00:06,730 --> 01:00:09,670
She speaks, and the lightning crashes!

952
01:00:12,490 --> 01:00:14,030
Hey, Jessica. Cheers.

953
01:00:16,660 --> 01:00:21,300
Hey, when I went up before, and you were in the bath...

954
01:00:21,300 --> 01:00:22,690
What about it?

955
01:00:23,780 --> 01:00:26,710
How to put it? You fit in here.

956
01:00:27,330 --> 01:00:30,280
This rich house suits you. Not like us.

957
01:00:30,280 --> 01:00:31,180
Fuck off.

958
01:00:31,180 --> 01:00:32,160
I'm serious!

959
01:00:32,160 --> 01:00:33,990
Dad, before...

960
01:00:33,990 --> 01:00:36,230
She was lying back in the tub, watching TV.

961
01:00:37,240 --> 01:00:39,200
Like she's lived here for years.

962
01:00:41,570 --> 01:00:42,940
Speaking of which,

963
01:00:44,110 --> 01:00:47,470
if this became our house,

964
01:00:47,470 --> 01:00:51,370
if we lived here, which room would you want?

965
01:00:51,830 --> 01:00:56,630
What room in this masterwork by the great Namgoong?

966
01:00:57,110 --> 01:00:59,090
Fuck, I don't know.

967
01:00:59,090 --> 01:01:02,120
Get me the house first. Then I'll think about it.

968
01:01:03,120 --> 01:01:05,030
We live here now, don't we?

969
01:01:05,860 --> 01:01:09,300
Getting drunk in the living room.

970
01:01:09,740 --> 01:01:12,890
Right, we live here. Why not?

971
01:01:12,890 --> 01:01:17,390
This is our home right now. It's cosy.

972
01:01:17,390 --> 01:01:20,160
Cosy? Are you feeling cosy?

973
01:01:20,750 --> 01:01:25,690
Sure, but suppose Park walked through that door now.

974
01:01:26,180 --> 01:01:27,690
What about your dad?

975
01:01:27,690 --> 01:01:30,720
He'd run and hide like a cockroach.

976
01:01:31,590 --> 01:01:34,780
Kids, you know at our house,

977
01:01:34,780 --> 01:01:39,440
when you turn on the light, and the cockroaches scatter?

978
01:01:39,890 --> 01:01:41,900
You know what I mean?

979
01:01:41,900 --> 01:01:45,130
I'm getting fucking tired of this.

980
01:01:46,200 --> 01:01:47,750
-A cockroach?    -Yeah.

981
01:01:49,860 --> 01:01:51,760
Huh? What's wrong?

982
01:01:51,760 --> 01:01:53,420
What's the matter?

983
01:01:54,900 --> 01:01:58,260
Dad, don't do that. You only live once.

984
01:02:05,900 --> 01:02:07,470
What the hell?

985
01:02:07,470 --> 01:02:09,510
I fooled you! Didn't I?

986
01:02:09,510 --> 01:02:10,890
Jesus, Dad.

987
01:02:10,890 --> 01:02:12,880
I fooled you too, Ki-woo?

988
01:02:12,880 --> 01:02:15,130
Did it look for real?

989
01:02:15,130 --> 01:02:17,890
If it was for real, I'd fucking kill you.

990
01:02:18,840 --> 01:02:20,070
What is this? Fucking puppy.

991
01:02:21,200 --> 01:02:22,540
Who is it at this hour'?

992
01:02:28,400 --> 01:02:30,510
What is it?

993
01:02:38,890 --> 01:02:40,430
What's she doing here?

994
01:02:41,060 --> 01:02:42,690
The old housekeeper?

995
01:02:43,410 --> 01:02:44,640
What's she here for?

996
01:02:45,640 --> 01:02:49,980
She won't stop ringing it.

997
01:02:51,620 --> 01:02:53,030
Raising a racket.

998
01:02:54,960 --> 01:02:55,930
Who is it?

999
01:02:57,390 --> 01:03:00,250
Oh, hello! I'm...

1000
01:03:00,840 --> 01:03:02,480
The madame's not in, right?

1001
01:03:02,480 --> 01:03:03,590
What?

1002
01:03:03,590 --> 01:03:07,630
I worked here for a very long time.

1003
01:03:08,580 --> 01:03:13,870
Above the monitor there, you see a photo of 3 dogs, right?

1004
01:03:14,350 --> 01:03:15,830
Zoome, Berry, Foofoo.

1005
01:03:15,830 --> 01:03:20,160
I get it, but why are you here?

1006
01:03:21,720 --> 01:03:24,650
You're my successor as housekeeper, right?

1007
01:03:30,050 --> 01:03:31,300
Anyway...

1008
01:03:32,530 --> 01:03:35,250
I'm very sorry to call on you so late.

1009
01:03:35,910 --> 01:03:37,250
It's just that...

1010
01:03:37,970 --> 01:03:44,700
I forgot something in the basement under the kitchen.

1011
01:03:45,490 --> 01:03:51,250
When I left, they pushed me out so quickly...

1012
01:03:55,110 --> 01:03:56,690
Would you let me in?

1013
01:03:59,190 --> 01:04:00,560
What do we do?

1014
01:04:01,750 --> 01:04:03,650
This isn't in the plan.

1015
01:04:11,590 --> 01:04:13,030
Sorry for the trouble.

1016
01:04:13,800 --> 01:04:15,100
This way.

1017
01:04:15,100 --> 01:04:16,700
Yes, thank you.

1018
01:04:19,390 --> 01:04:20,750
You can put your raincoat...

1019
01:04:20,750 --> 01:04:22,990
It'll just be a second.

1020
01:04:23,980 --> 01:04:27,630
Quite a meal there. That'll be a job to clean up.

1021
01:04:27,630 --> 01:04:30,640
But what did you leave below?

1022
01:04:35,510 --> 01:04:37,160
Want to come down with me?

1023
01:04:39,030 --> 01:04:41,830
Well, just go ahead.

1024
01:05:35,700 --> 01:05:39,200
Help me push this!

1025
01:05:39,200 --> 01:05:42,180
Pull it! From over there.

1026
01:05:42,210 --> 01:05:43,230
What?

1027
01:05:43,310 --> 01:05:44,480
Pull!

1028
01:05:46,790 --> 01:05:48,440
Pull it hard!

1029
01:05:52,230 --> 01:05:53,520
Are you okay?

1030
01:05:55,180 --> 01:05:56,870
Did I scare you?

1031
01:05:58,910 --> 01:06:00,640
Thank you!

1032
01:06:01,550 --> 01:06:02,790
Thank you.

1033
01:06:11,360 --> 01:06:12,180
Honey!

1034
01:06:12,260 --> 01:06:13,410
What the hell?

1035
01:06:14,980 --> 01:06:16,220
Hey!

1036
01:06:16,220 --> 01:06:17,510
Honey!

1037
01:06:18,580 --> 01:06:19,990
Honey!

1038
01:06:22,590 --> 01:06:23,830
Wait!

1039
01:06:23,830 --> 01:06:25,960
Honey, I'm here!

1040
01:06:26,030 --> 01:06:27,330
What is all this?

1041
01:06:29,870 --> 01:06:30,970
Honey!

1042
01:06:31,240 --> 01:06:32,890
Honey, I'm fine.

1043
01:06:32,990 --> 01:06:34,750
No you're not!

1044
01:06:34,850 --> 01:06:35,850
I'm fine, really.

1045
01:06:35,950 --> 01:06:37,190
How can you say that?

1046
01:06:37,480 --> 01:06:39,300
But I'm really hungry.

1047
01:06:39,300 --> 01:06:40,320
Suck it!

1048
01:06:40,320 --> 01:06:41,840
How many days has it been?

1049
01:06:42,430 --> 01:06:44,940
You must've been so hungry!

1050
01:06:47,260 --> 01:06:48,790
It's okay.

1051
01:06:48,790 --> 01:06:51,630
She's a nice woman. She let me in.

1052
01:06:51,630 --> 01:06:53,020
There was an iron plate, for grilling meat.

1053
01:06:53,020 --> 01:06:55,390
It was wedged under the shelf.

1054
01:06:55,390 --> 01:06:56,500
So that's why.

1055
01:06:56,500 --> 01:06:59,470
I couldn't open it from the inside.

1056
01:07:00,180 --> 01:07:01,510
What's going on here?

1057
01:07:01,510 --> 01:07:02,960
I know you must be startled.

1058
01:07:03,680 --> 01:07:06,110
I would be too in this situation.

1059
01:07:06,110 --> 01:07:11,030
But as two fellow workers... Right, Chung-sook?

1060
01:07:12,350 --> 01:07:14,320
How do you know my name?

1061
01:07:14,320 --> 01:07:18,480
To be honest I'm still texting with the boy Da-song.

1062
01:07:19,120 --> 01:07:21,030
I knew they were going camping,

1063
01:07:21,530 --> 01:07:23,850
so I came today.

1064
01:07:23,850 --> 01:07:26,140
I wanted to speak to you alone.

1065
01:07:26,770 --> 01:07:28,140
Talking about.

1066
01:07:30,300 --> 01:07:32,450
Don't worry, Chung-sook.

1067
01:07:34,450 --> 01:07:36,020
I cut the wire on the CCTV by the gate.

1068
01:07:36,720 --> 01:07:40,460
Nobody knows I came. Isn't that good, sis?

1069
01:07:41,170 --> 01:07:42,580
Don't call me sis!

1070
01:07:42,580 --> 01:07:45,180
Sis, my name is Moon-gwang.

1071
01:07:45,790 --> 01:07:50,230
This is my hubbie Oh Geun-sae. Say hello, honey.

1072
01:07:50,230 --> 01:07:53,900
This tastes great. What happened to your face?

1073
01:07:53,900 --> 01:07:56,380
I'll tell you later.

1074
01:07:57,020 --> 01:08:01,090
So you'd steal food every day while working in the kitchen.

1075
01:08:01,090 --> 01:08:02,230
Feeding your husband.

1076
01:08:02,230 --> 01:08:07,190
Not at all! I bought all his food with my salary.

1077
01:08:07,190 --> 01:08:10,140
That's so unfair!

1078
01:08:10,140 --> 01:08:12,850
But how long has your husband been down here?

1079
01:08:12,850 --> 01:08:14,850
Hold on a sec. 4 years?

1080
01:08:16,200 --> 01:08:19,070
4 years, 3 months and 17 days.

1081
01:08:19,070 --> 01:08:20,360
Right, it's June now.

1082
01:08:21,360 --> 01:08:26,880
Four years ago when Mr. Namgoong moved to Paris,

1083
01:08:27,510 --> 01:08:30,160
in the time before Mr. Park's family moved in,

1084
01:08:30,710 --> 01:08:34,150
I brought my husband down here.

1085
01:08:34,150 --> 01:08:38,770
Many rich houses have secret bunkers, where you can hide

1086
01:08:39,330 --> 01:08:42,240
in case North Korea attacks,

1087
01:08:42,240 --> 01:08:44,070
or if creditors break in.

1088
01:08:44,070 --> 01:08:48,820
But it seems Mr. Namgoong was a bit embarrassed about this,

1089
01:08:48,820 --> 01:08:53,250
because he never mentioned it to Mr. Park's family.

1090
01:08:53,250 --> 01:08:55,910
So only I know about it.

1091
01:08:55,910 --> 01:08:57,690
So that's how it happened.

1092
01:08:58,310 --> 01:09:00,710
But now that I know,

1093
01:09:00,710 --> 01:09:02,900
I've no choice but to call the police!

1094
01:09:02,900 --> 01:09:04,350
No please, sis!

1095
01:09:05,590 --> 01:09:07,870
As fellow members of the needy, please don't.

1096
01:09:07,870 --> 01:09:09,870
I'm not needy!

1097
01:09:09,870 --> 01:09:13,330
But we're needy!

1098
01:09:13,330 --> 01:09:17,240
We've no house, no money, only debts!

1099
01:09:17,970 --> 01:09:19,150
Sis, please!

1100
01:09:19,150 --> 01:09:23,650
Even after 4 years of hiding, those debt collectors won't give up.

1101
01:09:23,650 --> 01:09:28,020
They're still searching for him, threatening to stab him.

1102
01:09:28,020 --> 01:09:29,340
You used loan sharks?

1103
01:09:30,480 --> 01:09:32,130
It's all my fault.

1104
01:09:32,890 --> 01:09:36,630
The Taiwan cake shop.

1105
01:09:36,630 --> 01:09:38,990
My Taiwanese Wangshui castella shop went bust.

1106
01:09:38,990 --> 01:09:40,760
I was overwhelmed by debt.

1107
01:09:41,260 --> 01:09:42,470
Please take this.

1108
01:09:43,180 --> 01:09:44,170
What's that?

1109
01:09:44,780 --> 01:09:48,990
It's not much, just a modest sum.

1110
01:09:48,990 --> 01:09:51,310
But we'll send it to you every month.

1111
01:09:52,100 --> 01:09:54,090
In return, just once every 2 days.

1112
01:09:54,090 --> 01:09:56,840
please leave him some food.

1113
01:09:57,830 --> 01:10:01,340
No no, just once a week.

1114
01:10:01,340 --> 01:10:03,660
There's a refrigerator here. Just once a week.

1115
01:10:03,660 --> 01:10:06,820
You've got some nerve! I'm calling the police.

1116
01:10:06,820 --> 01:10:08,210
Sis!

1117
01:10:10,180 --> 01:10:11,210
Who is that?

1118
01:10:14,620 --> 01:10:16,060
Wait... Jessica?

1119
01:10:17,190 --> 01:10:18,390
Mr. Kim?

1120
01:10:18,390 --> 01:10:19,470
What the hell?

1121
01:10:20,620 --> 01:10:22,710
Dad, my ankle!

1122
01:10:22,710 --> 01:10:23,820
You okay? Sorry.

1123
01:10:23,820 --> 01:10:25,750
Dad, my foot.

1124
01:10:25,750 --> 01:10:27,750
Don't call me Dad!

1125
01:10:34,310 --> 01:10:37,990
I thought it was weird when the driver was fired.

1126
01:10:39,120 --> 01:10:39,910
Hey.

1127
01:10:39,910 --> 01:10:42,380
-Let's talk things over.    -What the hell?

1128
01:10:42,380 --> 01:10:43,760
Are you some family of charlatans?

1129
01:10:43,760 --> 01:10:44,710
So, sis...

1130
01:10:44,710 --> 01:10:46,740
Don't fucking call me sis, you filthy bitch!

1131
01:10:47,470 --> 01:10:52,720
I'm gonna send this video to the madame, how about that?

1132
01:10:52,720 --> 01:10:54,720
Dad, my foot.

1133
01:10:54,720 --> 01:10:56,780
No reception in the basement, right?

1134
01:10:57,630 --> 01:10:59,630
-The phone works fine.    -Fuck.

1135
01:10:59,630 --> 01:11:04,390
Ma'am, to be honest, the jobs we have here...

1136
01:11:04,390 --> 01:11:07,510
Shut up! It's too late now!

1137
01:11:07,510 --> 01:11:09,510
Let's all go to jail!

1138
01:11:09,510 --> 01:11:10,870
We're fucking going down!

1139
01:11:10,870 --> 01:11:13,660
Lady, are you crazy?

1140
01:11:14,630 --> 01:11:19,360
If they see that video, Mr. Park and his wife will be so shocked!

1141
01:11:19,950 --> 01:11:22,560
What did those nice people ever do wrong?

1142
01:11:23,910 --> 01:11:24,940
Why do this to them?

1143
01:11:24,940 --> 01:11:25,960
Stop right there!

1144
01:11:26,590 --> 01:11:28,440
Or I'll push the 'send' button.

1145
01:11:29,030 --> 01:11:30,020
Follow me.

1146
01:11:31,230 --> 01:11:33,590
Calm down, ma'am.

1147
01:11:34,670 --> 01:11:36,310
Don't push!

1148
01:11:40,430 --> 01:11:41,930
Let's go up, honey.

1149
01:11:42,470 --> 01:11:45,350
Time for you to get some fresh air!

1150
01:12:02,510 --> 01:12:08,120
Honey, this 'send' button is like a missile launcher.

1151
01:12:09,070 --> 01:12:11,230
What do you mean, honey?

1152
01:12:11,230 --> 01:12:16,760
If we threaten to push it. those people can't do anything.

1153
01:12:16,760 --> 01:12:21,040
It's like a North Korean rocket. A North Korean missile button!

1154
01:12:22,550 --> 01:12:26,500
Today our beloved Great Leader Kim Jong-un,

1155
01:12:26,500 --> 01:12:29,550
after witnessing the charlatan family video,

1156
01:12:29,550 --> 01:12:32,350
was unable to contain his shock and fury

1157
01:12:32,350 --> 01:12:35,620
at their wicked, despicable provocation!

1158
01:12:35,620 --> 01:12:37,560
I've missed your jokes, honey!

1159
01:12:37,560 --> 01:12:39,400
Therefore our Great Leader,

1160
01:12:39,400 --> 01:12:42,220
in this age of denuclearization,

1161
01:12:42,220 --> 01:12:48,160
has commanded that the nation's last remaining nuclear warhead

1162
01:12:48,160 --> 01:12:50,710
be driven down the throats of this wicked family!

1163
01:12:50,710 --> 01:12:55,440
No one can imitate North Korean news anchors like you!

1164
01:12:55,440 --> 01:12:58,940
With their stinking guts serving as the last nuclear graveyard,

1165
01:12:58,940 --> 01:13:05,620
our Dear Leaders wish to denuclearize and bring world peace can...

1166
01:13:05,620 --> 01:13:06,920
Hands in the air, fuckers!

1167
01:13:07,790 --> 01:13:08,920
Higher!

1168
01:13:11,200 --> 01:13:13,270
You scumbag family.

1169
01:13:13,270 --> 01:13:14,680
Husband?

1170
01:13:14,680 --> 01:13:15,420
Husband.

1171
01:13:15,420 --> 01:13:16,380
Wife?

1172
01:13:16,380 --> 01:13:17,260
Yes.

1173
01:13:17,260 --> 01:13:18,430
Son?

1174
01:13:18,430 --> 01:13:18,980
Yes.

1175
01:13:18,980 --> 01:13:19,700
Daughter?

1176
01:13:19,700 --> 01:13:20,360
Yes.

1177
01:13:20,360 --> 01:13:22,460
You neanderthals.

1178
01:13:22,460 --> 01:13:26,020
Is that all you can think to do, drink yourselves stupid?

1179
01:13:26,880 --> 01:13:31,460
In this home suffused with Mr. Namgoong's creative spirit?

1180
01:13:32,150 --> 01:13:33,350
You cretins!

1181
01:13:33,350 --> 01:13:34,840
What do you know about art?

1182
01:13:34,840 --> 01:13:36,840
What would they know?

1183
01:13:37,750 --> 01:13:40,360
When the sun was nice,

1184
01:13:40,360 --> 01:13:44,750
we'd bask in those sunbeam, right?

1185
01:13:46,420 --> 01:13:50,390
At such moments we could feel his artistic touch.

1186
01:15:00,950 --> 01:15:02,080
Give it to me!

1187
01:15:02,080 --> 01:15:05,430
Good job! Delete it!

1188
01:15:05,430 --> 01:15:09,040
Careful, don't send it by accident.

1189
01:15:23,070 --> 01:15:24,020
Hello?

1190
01:15:24,950 --> 01:15:27,940
Listen, do you know how to make ram-don?

1191
01:15:28,920 --> 01:15:30,260
Ram-don?

1192
01:15:30,260 --> 01:15:33,320
Da-song likes ram-don more than anything.

1193
01:15:34,080 --> 01:15:37,880
If you boil the water now, the timing will be perfect.

1194
01:15:37,880 --> 01:15:40,720
There's sirloin in the fridge, add that too.

1195
01:15:40,720 --> 01:15:43,000
Then, the camping...?

1196
01:15:43,000 --> 01:15:45,280
My god, what a disaster.

1197
01:15:46,520 --> 01:15:51,960
The river overflowed and everyone was packing their tents,

1198
01:15:51,960 --> 01:15:55,140
but Da-song was crying and refusing to go home.

1199
01:15:55,880 --> 01:15:58,670
Anyway, ram-don as soon as we walk in, okay?

1200
01:15:59,460 --> 01:16:01,960
Then you're almost here?

1201
01:16:01,960 --> 01:16:04,880
8 minutes, according to the GPS.

1202
01:16:04,880 --> 01:16:06,000
You arrive in 8 minutes...

1203
01:16:06,000 --> 01:16:09,280
Start boiling the water right away!

1204
01:16:13,680 --> 01:16:14,950
What the hell is ram-don?

1205
01:16:24,300 --> 01:16:25,870
Move, quickly!

1206
01:16:27,230 --> 01:16:29,390
Hurry!

1207
01:16:36,280 --> 01:16:37,220
Ramen/Udon.

1208
01:16:39,320 --> 01:16:42,160
Dad, I can't drag her any further!

1209
01:16:53,120 --> 01:16:55,110
What are you doing?

1210
01:16:56,550 --> 01:16:58,190
Dad!

1211
01:17:01,300 --> 01:17:04,230
Go up quickly! Help upstairs.

1212
01:17:12,200 --> 01:17:13,540
Take this!

1213
01:17:31,920 --> 01:17:34,030
Welcome home!

1214
01:17:34,030 --> 01:17:37,120
Da-song, look! Let's eat ram-don!

1215
01:17:39,680 --> 01:17:40,760
Da-song!

1216
01:17:44,390 --> 01:17:45,960
Da-song!

1217
01:17:47,160 --> 01:17:48,320
Madame!

1218
01:18:11,790 --> 01:18:14,150
Why don't you just eat the ram-don?

1219
01:18:14,150 --> 01:18:15,020
Shall I?

1220
01:18:15,020 --> 01:18:18,230
No, wait. I can give it to my husband.

1221
01:18:18,230 --> 01:18:19,830
There's sirloin in here.

1222
01:18:22,780 --> 01:18:25,830
It's cooked through? Medium well done.

1223
01:18:51,080 --> 01:18:55,950
Returning after a day's work... I love you so much, Mr. Park!

1224
01:18:59,500 --> 01:19:03,460
Home from the office, Mr. Park is off duty now.

1225
01:19:05,840 --> 01:19:10,150
Returning after a day's work... I love you so much, Mr. Park!

1226
01:19:10,150 --> 01:19:11,980
-What are you doing?    -Shut up!

1227
01:19:23,710 --> 01:19:26,360
Honey, do you want some ram-don?

1228
01:19:26,360 --> 01:19:27,460
Da-song doesn't want it?

1229
01:19:27,460 --> 01:19:28,180
No.

1230
01:19:28,180 --> 01:19:30,480
No, I'm tired. I'm going to bed.

1231
01:19:30,480 --> 01:19:33,160
Why are you staring?

1232
01:19:34,460 --> 01:19:38,080
Mr. Park, you feed me and house me.

1233
01:19:38,080 --> 01:19:39,920
Respect!

1234
01:19:41,510 --> 01:19:43,080
You do this every day?

1235
01:19:43,760 --> 01:19:48,760
Sure, I even send whole sentences to thank him.

1236
01:19:50,070 --> 01:19:52,040
Someone of your age should know it.

1237
01:19:52,040 --> 01:19:53,070
Know what?

1238
01:19:53,070 --> 01:19:54,310
Morse Code.

1239
01:19:55,360 --> 01:19:58,820
That sensor's going batty.

1240
01:20:07,550 --> 01:20:11,120
Da-song will know it, since he's a Scout.

1241
01:20:11,120 --> 01:20:12,980
It's ridiculous, right?

1242
01:20:12,980 --> 01:20:15,950
Running around. trying to please a kid.

1243
01:20:16,550 --> 01:20:18,150
He's not some kind of prince.

1244
01:20:18,640 --> 01:20:21,070
He's the youngest. It's common.

1245
01:20:22,430 --> 01:20:23,710
Please understand.

1246
01:20:24,400 --> 01:20:27,540
Da-song's a bit... unwell.

1247
01:20:28,540 --> 01:20:31,150
He's receiving trauma therapy and art therapy.

1248
01:20:32,460 --> 01:20:34,550
There was an incident.

1249
01:20:34,550 --> 01:20:35,760
What incident?

1250
01:20:36,320 --> 01:20:39,100
Sis, you believe in ghosts, too?

1251
01:20:41,260 --> 01:20:44,560
Da-song saw a ghost in the house when he was in 1st grade.

1252
01:20:51,440 --> 01:20:54,320
He had a birthday party at home that day.

1253
01:20:54,320 --> 01:20:56,900
Late that night, when everyone was sleeping,

1254
01:20:56,900 --> 01:21:01,560
Da-song crept down to the kitchen and took the cake out.

1255
01:21:01,560 --> 01:21:04,430
The whipped cream on that cake was amazing.

1256
01:21:04,430 --> 01:21:06,840
Even in bed, he couldn't stop thinking about it.

1257
01:21:07,870 --> 01:21:12,960
So Da-song was sitting, eating his cake...

1258
01:21:21,800 --> 01:21:25,760
He screamed, and I ran downstairs,

1259
01:21:26,540 --> 01:21:28,070
and he was all...

1260
01:21:29,060 --> 01:21:33,960
his eyes rolled back in his head, convulsions, foam in his mouth.

1261
01:21:36,340 --> 01:21:38,740
Have you ever seen a child have a seizure?

1262
01:21:38,740 --> 01:21:39,640
No.

1263
01:21:39,640 --> 01:21:44,270
They need 15-minute treatment, or they're done for.

1264
01:21:44,960 --> 01:21:48,560
That's the time you have to reach an emergency room, 15 minutes.

1265
01:21:50,420 --> 01:21:55,960
How can you live in a place like this?

1266
01:21:55,960 --> 01:21:59,340
Well, lots of people live underground.

1267
01:21:59,340 --> 01:22:01,270
Especially if you count semi-basements.

1268
01:22:01,270 --> 01:22:05,350
What'll you do? You don't have a plan?

1269
01:22:06,120 --> 01:22:09,180
I just feel comfortable here.

1270
01:22:10,760 --> 01:22:13,630
It feels like I was born here.

1271
01:22:14,640 --> 01:22:17,300
Maybe I had my wedding here, too.

1272
01:22:18,060 --> 01:22:20,910
As for the National Pension, I don't qualify.

1273
01:22:22,550 --> 01:22:25,550
In my old age, love will comfort me.

1274
01:22:27,620 --> 01:22:32,390
So please. Let me live down here.

1275
01:22:34,640 --> 01:22:35,660
Anyway...

1276
01:22:36,910 --> 01:22:41,860
My husband was away on business, so I had to deal with it all.

1277
01:22:42,620 --> 01:22:47,030
Since then we've always gone out for his birthday.

1278
01:22:47,060 --> 01:22:50,190
Last year my mother's house, this year, camping.

1279
01:22:50,190 --> 01:22:55,160
Da-song's dad says it's just a part of growing up.

1280
01:22:55,160 --> 01:22:59,020
They say a ghost in the house brings wealth.

1281
01:23:01,150 --> 01:23:05,340
Actually, the money's been good recently.

1282
01:23:32,700 --> 01:23:34,600
Thank god.

1283
01:24:01,100 --> 01:24:03,480
Just stay here for now.

1284
01:24:14,750 --> 01:24:16,660
Zoonie, what's wrong?

1285
01:24:19,320 --> 01:24:20,520
Something under there?

1286
01:24:21,950 --> 01:24:23,630
What is it?

1287
01:24:24,340 --> 01:24:25,630
Damn it!

1288
01:24:27,500 --> 01:24:28,720
-Mom!    -Yeah?

1289
01:24:28,720 --> 01:24:31,190
-How could you?    -What?

1290
01:24:31,190 --> 01:24:32,800
I like ram-don too!

1291
01:24:32,800 --> 01:24:34,940
How could you not even ask me?

1292
01:24:34,940 --> 01:24:35,640
Well...

1293
01:24:35,640 --> 01:24:38,760
Da-song didn't want it, so you asked Dad,

1294
01:24:38,760 --> 01:24:40,360
then ate it yourself.

1295
01:24:40,360 --> 01:24:42,340
Want her to make one?

1296
01:24:42,340 --> 01:24:44,160
That's not the point!

1297
01:24:44,160 --> 01:24:47,140
-Stop fighting over ramen!    -Why didn't you ask me?

1298
01:24:47,140 --> 01:24:48,830
Oh, stop it! Just go to bed Go get changed.

1299
01:24:49,600 --> 01:24:50,830
This way!

1300
01:24:57,580 --> 01:24:58,340
Ki-jung?

1301
01:24:58,340 --> 01:24:59,680
Under there! Hurry!

1302
01:25:02,780 --> 01:25:07,140
One, two, three! One two three!

1303
01:25:07,140 --> 01:25:09,350
Da-song?

1304
01:25:09,350 --> 01:25:11,020
Da-song, cut it out!

1305
01:25:11,020 --> 01:25:14,560
He's gone crazy! Get an umbrella.

1306
01:25:14,560 --> 01:25:16,160
Hey Park Da-song!

1307
01:25:17,580 --> 01:25:21,350
What a monster. What the hell is he doing?

1308
01:25:22,470 --> 01:25:27,040
Da-song, it's time for bed! You know how late it is?

1309
01:25:27,050 --> 01:25:28,240
Here.

1310
01:25:28,340 --> 01:25:29,710
Honey, here.

1311
01:25:33,260 --> 01:25:38,640
Who do you take after to be so stubborn! Look at this rain!

1312
01:25:45,340 --> 01:25:47,820
OMG Kevin. Da-song camping in the yard.

1313
01:25:51,900 --> 01:25:54,790
Hey, channel 3 for emergencies!

1314
01:25:54,790 --> 01:25:56,840
Keep it turned on.

1315
01:25:56,840 --> 01:26:00,120
Let me have it. I can't believe him.

1316
01:26:00,120 --> 01:26:02,940
Just leave him. He'll come in if he's tired.

1317
01:26:03,120 --> 01:26:06,210
-I want you here, honey.    -I'm with you.

1318
01:26:06,220 --> 01:26:07,180
Hey, Da-hye!

1319
01:26:07,280 --> 01:26:09,880
Stop using your phone. Go to bed.

1320
01:26:10,060 --> 01:26:12,760
Go sleep in your room. We'll take care of things.

1321
01:26:14,030 --> 01:26:16,080
This is the living room, do you copy?

1322
01:26:16,080 --> 01:26:17,380
Copy, over.

1323
01:26:17,380 --> 01:26:21,420
Daddy is standing by for emergencies, over.

1324
01:26:21,420 --> 01:26:23,740
Got it, over.

1325
01:26:25,310 --> 01:26:27,480
Is that tent going to leak?

1326
01:26:27,480 --> 01:26:30,750
We ordered from the U.S., it'll be fine.

1327
01:26:30,750 --> 01:26:33,960
-Should we sleep here?    -What?

1328
01:26:33,960 --> 01:26:36,200
We've got a full view of the tent.

1329
01:26:36,200 --> 01:26:38,190
Good idea. I'll feel much better.

1330
01:26:38,190 --> 01:26:38,950
Right?

1331
01:26:38,950 --> 01:26:40,600
Let's watch over him as we sleep.

1332
01:26:43,070 --> 01:26:44,640
What a kid...

1333
01:26:53,900 --> 01:26:55,630
Wait a minute.

1334
01:26:57,630 --> 01:27:00,150
Where's that smell coming from?

1335
01:27:00,150 --> 01:27:01,510
What smell?

1336
01:27:01,510 --> 01:27:03,400
Mr. Kim's smell.

1337
01:27:03,400 --> 01:27:05,230
-Mr. Kim?    -Yeah.

1338
01:27:05,790 --> 01:27:07,230
Not sure what you mean.

1339
01:27:07,230 --> 01:27:09,960
Really? You must have smelled it.

1340
01:27:10,620 --> 01:27:14,590
That smell that wafts through the car, how to describe it?

1341
01:27:14,620 --> 01:27:17,460
-An old man's smell?    -No no, it's not that.

1342
01:27:17,460 --> 01:27:19,100
What is it?

1343
01:27:19,750 --> 01:27:21,430
Like an old radish?

1344
01:27:22,350 --> 01:27:23,110
No.

1345
01:27:23,760 --> 01:27:25,360
You know when you boil a rag?

1346
01:27:25,360 --> 01:27:26,740
It smells like that.

1347
01:27:29,980 --> 01:27:35,670
Anyway, even though he always seems about to cross the line,

1348
01:27:35,670 --> 01:27:39,760
