1620
01:55:54,030 --> 01:55:58,630
You have the right to an attorney...

1621
01:55:58,630 --> 01:56:02,550
Who looked nothing like a detective.

1622
01:56:05,400 --> 01:56:06,790
Is he laughing?

1623
01:56:07,580 --> 01:56:08,620
Just a sec.

1624
01:56:09,630 --> 01:56:13,660
Then the doctor who looked nothing like a doctor spoke.

1625
01:56:15,520 --> 01:56:19,440
That happens sometimes after brain surgery.

1626
01:56:19,440 --> 01:56:21,440
They keep laughing. For no reason.

1627
01:56:22,220 --> 01:56:24,120
Do you hear me?

1628
01:56:24,660 --> 01:56:26,120
Can you hear me?

1629
01:56:26,720 --> 01:56:28,620
Then do I have to do it again?

1630
01:56:28,620 --> 01:56:29,500
Do what?

1631
01:56:29,500 --> 01:56:30,790
The Miranda thing.

1632
01:56:33,310 --> 01:56:36,310
You have the right to remain silent.

1633
01:56:36,310 --> 01:56:40,380
Anything you say can and will be used against you...

1634
01:56:40,380 --> 01:56:42,380
He keeps laughing, look!

1635
01:56:45,670 --> 01:56:50,940
Even when I heard how much Ki-jung bled that day...

1636
01:56:51,660 --> 01:56:54,100
Even when I heard the words forgery,

1637
01:56:54,100 --> 01:56:58,830
trespassing, foul play, self-defense

1638
01:56:59,710 --> 01:57:05,220
and we were lucky to get away with a probation...

1639
01:57:08,870 --> 01:57:12,180
Even when I finally got to see Ki-jung's face...

1640
01:57:12,200 --> 01:57:14,700
Kim Ki-jung. RIP.

1641
01:57:16,480 --> 01:57:18,460
I kept laughing.

1642
01:57:28,590 --> 01:57:33,560
Still, when I went back and watched the news reports,

1643
01:57:34,180 --> 01:57:35,870
I didn't laugh.

1644
01:57:36,280 --> 01:57:38,750
This sudden rampage in the back yard of an upper-class home

1645
01:57:38,750 --> 01:57:40,700
is a highly unusual case.

1646
01:57:40,700 --> 01:57:46,020
Since the homeless man who sparked the rampage died at the scene,

1647
01:57:46,020 --> 01:57:51,310
police are struggling to even establish a clear motive.

1648
01:57:51,310 --> 01:57:55,880
The driver Kim and the slain
Mr. Park are said to have been on good terms.

1649
01:57:55,880 --> 01:58:00,860
For now the police investigation
is focused on locating the driver Kim.

1650
01:58:01,950 --> 01:58:06,070
Kim, after exiting this door and descending the stairs,

1651
01:58:06,070 --> 01:58:08,710
disappeared into the neighboring alleys.

1652
01:58:09,800 --> 01:58:14,420
Police searched the CCTVs of nearby homes to no avail,

1653
01:58:15,380 --> 01:58:17,990
and they have yet to find any witnesses.

1654
01:58:19,040 --> 01:58:21,270
Given the situation,

1655
01:58:21,270 --> 01:58:25,600
it's not an exaggeration to say that Kim vanished into thin air.

1656
01:58:27,600 --> 01:58:34,590
Actually Mom and I had no idea where Dad was.

1657
01:58:36,910 --> 01:58:42,040
But those detectives still wore themselves out tailing us.

1658
01:58:46,480 --> 01:58:51,990
Eventually the news went quiet, and after the tails stopped,

1659
01:58:53,030 --> 01:58:56,430
I started going up that mountain.

1660
01:58:58,430 --> 01:59:02,880
From up there, you get a great view of the house.

1661
01:59:06,140 --> 01:59:09,500
That day, despite the cold.

1662
01:59:10,660 --> 01:59:12,710
I felt like staying longer.

1663
01:59:26,280 --> 01:59:29,390
Dash-dash-dot-dot.

1664
01:59:34,100 --> 01:59:52,200
Dash-dash-dot-dot.

1665
01:59:55,190 --> 01:59:56,100
Son!

1666
01:59:58,560 --> 01:59:59,760
Son!

1667
02:00:02,080 --> 02:00:05,270
Perhaps you, if no one else. will be able to read this letter.

1668
02:00:09,180 --> 02:00:14,640
You were a Boy Scout, so I'm writing this just in case.

1669
02:00:18,750 --> 02:00:20,980
Have your injuries healed?

1670
02:00:22,640 --> 02:00:26,120
I'm sure your mom is plenty healthy.

1671
02:00:30,870 --> 02:00:33,340
I'm doing fine in here.

1672
02:00:34,710 --> 02:00:37,120
Though thinking of Ki-jung makes me cry.

1673
02:00:40,670 --> 02:00:44,780
Even now, what happened that day doesn't seem real.

1674
02:00:46,680 --> 02:00:48,510
It feels like a dream,

1675
02:00:49,990 --> 02:00:51,670
and yet it doesn't.

1676
02:00:53,320 --> 02:00:57,550
That day as I went out the gate, I suddenly knew.

1677
02:00:58,800 --> 02:01:00,480
Where I needed to go...

1678
02:01:40,260 --> 02:01:43,460
A house where such grisly crime took place

1679
02:01:43,460 --> 02:01:46,220
would surely not be easy to sell.

1680
02:01:49,790 --> 02:01:51,740
I'm sorry, Mr. Park.

1681
02:01:52,390 --> 02:01:57,840
I struggled to hold out like that in an empty house.

1682
02:02:01,380 --> 02:02:04,430
Still, thanks to the house being empty.

1683
02:02:04,430 --> 02:02:09,390
what was her name? Moon-gwang?

1684
02:02:09,390 --> 02:02:12,880
I was able to give her a proper send off.

1685
02:02:14,830 --> 02:02:20,450
I hear tree-side burials are trendy. so hell, I did my best.

1686
02:02:24,820 --> 02:02:28,120
But those real estate sharks sure are clever.

1687
02:02:33,040 --> 02:02:37,540
They hoodwinked some people who had just arrived in Korea

1688
02:02:37,540 --> 02:02:39,240
and managed to sell the house.

1689
02:02:40,960 --> 02:02:44,270
With the parents working, and the kids attending school,

1690
02:02:44,270 --> 02:02:47,100
the family is usually out.

1691
02:02:47,100 --> 02:02:51,800
But the goddamned housekeeper stays there 24 hours a day.

1692
02:02:52,640 --> 02:02:56,870
Each time I go upstairs, I take my life in my hands.

1693
02:03:00,040 --> 02:03:03,710
It turns out Germans eat more than just sausage and beer.

1694
02:03:04,820 --> 02:03:06,430
What a relief.

1695
02:03:09,630 --> 02:03:13,200
Passing the time down here, everything starts to go hazy.

1696
02:03:18,160 --> 02:03:21,830
Today at least I was able to write you a letter.

1697
02:03:24,240 --> 02:03:28,110
If I send out the letter this way every night,

1698
02:03:28,110 --> 02:03:32,320
maybe someday you'll see it.

1699
02:03:38,520 --> 02:03:40,040
So long.

1700
02:03:54,200 --> 02:03:55,560
You're home, Ki-woo?

1701
02:03:55,560 --> 02:03:56,540
Yeah.

1702
02:04:10,900 --> 02:04:15,180
Dad, today I made a plan.

1703
02:04:17,280 --> 02:04:19,110
A fundamental plan.

1704
02:04:22,270 --> 02:04:23,640
I'm going to earn money.

1705
02:04:24,820 --> 02:04:25,910
A lot of it.

1706
02:04:29,870 --> 02:04:33,910
University, a career, marriage. those are all fine,

1707
02:04:34,860 --> 02:04:36,880
but first I'll earn money.

1708
02:04:36,880 --> 02:04:41,820
You'll see once you go in, but it's very spacious.

1709
02:04:42,880 --> 02:04:47,710
Actually, we don't show this house to just anyone.

1710
02:04:47,710 --> 02:04:51,540
When I have money, I'll buy that house.

1711
02:04:53,060 --> 02:04:57,020
On the day we move in, Mom and I will be in the yard.

1712
02:04:57,980 --> 02:04:59,820
Because the sunshine is so nice there.

1713
02:05:01,580 --> 02:05:02,830
All you'll need to do

1714
02:05:03,790 --> 02:05:05,620
is walk up the stairs.

1715
02:06:29,480 --> 02:06:33,540
Take care until then.

1716
02:06:38,160 --> 02:06:40,750
So long.